Project Overview
This project is a simple static website developed using HTML.
It represents the IPL Auction 2026 by displaying team details, player information, auction prices, and sold players in a structured format.

Features
Displays IPL team list
Shows player details with prices
Uses tables for structured data
Includes team selection dropdown
Displays team images
Provides simple auction form
Shows sold players list
Easy navigation using internal links

Problem Statement
Manual presentation of IPL auction data is not well organized. A static website is required to present team and player details in a clear and structured format.

Objective
To create a webpage using HTML
To display structured data using lists and tables
To use forms and input elements
To improve understanding of webpage design
Tools Used
HTML5
VS Code / Notepad

Description
This project demonstrates a static IPL auction website created using basic HTML elements.
It includes sections such as team list, player tables, images, and an auction form.

The webpage uses:
Lists to display teams
Tables to show player details
Images for visual representation
Forms for user input

Algorithm
Start
Create HTML structure
Add heading and description
Display IPL teams using list
Add dropdown for team selection
Show images using image tag
Display players using tables
Create auction form
Show sold players list
End

Conclusion
This project shows how HTML can be used to build a simple static website. It helps in understanding webpage structure, elements, and layout design.
